  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>Necromantic energy washes over a creature of your choice that you can see within range, draining moisture and vitality from it. The target must make a &amp;Reference[con]{Constitution} saving throw. The target takes 8d8 &amp;Reference[necrotic]{necrotic} damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. This spell has no effect on &amp;Reference[undead]{undead} or constructs.</p>\n<p>If you target a &amp;Reference[plant]{plant} creature or a magical &amp;Reference[plant]{plant}, it makes the saving throw with disadvantage, and the spell deals maximum damage to it.</p>\n<p>If you target a nonmagical &amp;Reference[plant]{plant} that isn't a creature, such as a tree or shrub, it doesn't make a saving throw; it simply withers and dies.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 4th.</p>\n</div>",
